03/12/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Miroslav Cimpl, the driver who crashed into Serbian President Boris Tadic's convoy earlier this week, has been detained for 48 hours, local media reported Thursday (2 December). 
Belgrade District Court issued the detention order to keep Cimpl in custody until the investigation is complete. 
The news comes amid efforts to clarify whether the incident was simply a traffic accident or an assassination attempt. 
Cimpl is an employee of the US Embassy in Belgrade. 
(B92, Tanjug - 02/12/04)
